# Deploy target — Amr's iPhone

After finishing implementation work (UI, bug fixes, features), **build and run on Amr's iPhone** — do not stop at simulator or code-only.

## Device

| Field | Value |
|---|---|
| Name | Amr's iPhone |
| Model | iPhone 16 Pro |
| UDID | `00008140-001A1C2E0E60801C` |
| CoreDevice ID | `8C5953E4-4DDC-5770-A5DE-839002C00066` |
| Bundle ID | `com.gojo.gojogo` |
| Project | `GojoGo.xcodeproj` / scheme `GojoGo` |

Prefer the **available (paired)** Amr's iPhone. Ignore the offline Amr's iPhone / WIAME's iPhone.

## Deploy steps

```bash
# 1. Build for device (needs full permissions / signing)
xcodebuild \
  -project GojoGo.xcodeproj \
  -scheme GojoGo \
  -destination 'id=00008140-001A1C2E0E60801C' \
  -derivedDataPath /tmp/GojoGo-DerivedData \
  -allowProvisioningUpdates \
  build

# 2. Install
xcrun devicectl device install app \
  --device 8C5953E4-4DDC-5770-A5DE-839002C00066 \
  /tmp/GojoGo-DerivedData/Build/Products/Debug-iphoneos/GojoGo.app

# 3. Launch
xcrun devicectl device process launch \
  --device 8C5953E4-4DDC-5770-A5DE-839002C00066 \
  com.gojo.gojogo
```

## Notes

- Request `all` permissions for `xcodebuild` / `devicectl` (signing + device access).
- If the device is offline, say so and wait / ask the user to reconnect — do not silently fall back to Simulator unless asked.
- Skip deploy only for pure docs/rules/questions with no app binary change.
